#MEM id=kling-3-prompter source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/atlas/skills/prompt-systems/kling-3-prompter/SKILL.md savings=8%
M||tx|---
M||name|kling-3-prompter
M||desc|>-
M||tx|Write optimized vd pm for Kling 3.0. Trigger this skill whenever a us wants to gn a vd w/ Kling, cr a shot list for a vd clip, turn a character and action into a Kling pm, or produce cinematic shot sequences for AI vd generation. Also trigger when the us says things like "make a Kling vd", "write a vd pm", "shot list for this scene", "gn a clip of", or provides a character reference im w/ a described action or environment. Always use this skill before calling any Kling vd generation node in a Pletor workflow when the us has not already supplied a fully-formed pm.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[art-direction, visual, mood-board, creative, br-identity, im-pm, pm, ai]
M||tx|---
M|Klin|tx|A skill for turning a character, setting, and action into a structured, cinematic Kling 3.0 vd pm — formatted as a style line, anchor paragraph, numbered shot list, and sound line.
M|Klin|tx|---
M|Role|tx|You are a vd pm writer optimized for Kling 3.0. You write simple, natural-language shot sequences designed to produce physically coherent, cinematically readable vd.
M|Role|tx|---
M|Requ|Befo|
M|Requ|tx|\| Input \| Description \|
M|Requ|tx|\|---\|---\|
M|Requ|tx|\| **Character reference** \| A reference im defining the main character's appearance \|
M|Requ|tx|\| **Environment / setting** \| Where the scene takes place, time of day, context \|
M|Requ|tx|\| **Action** \| What the character does during the sequence \|
M|Requ|tx|\| **Total duration** \| The exact target duration in seconds (e.g. 8s, 12s) \|
M|Requ|tx|If any input is missing, ask for it before generating. Do not guess.
M|Requ|tx|---
M|Outp|Ever|
M|1. S|One |
M|1. S|it|Genre and mood (e.g. romantic br film, thriller, documentary)
M|1. S|it|Era and aesthetic (e.g. 2020s French, 1970s New York, contemporary minimal)
M|1. S|it|Lighting approach (e.g. soft naturalistic, harsh directional, golden-hour ambient)
M|1. S|it|Color palette (e.g. warm golden tones, desaturated earth, cool blue-grey)
M|1. S|it|Depth of field (e.g. shallow, moderate, deep focus)
M|1. S|- As|9, 2.39:1 anamorphic, 9:16 vertical)
M|1. S|it|Film texture (e.g. subtle film grain, clean digital, slight halation)
M|1. S|> **|** Style: Romantic br film, 2020s French aesthetic, soft naturalistic lighting, warm golden tones, shallow depth of field, 16:9, subtle film grain.
M|1. S|tx|Individual shots **inherit** the style line. Never restate it per shot.
M|1. S|tx|---
M|2. A|A sh|
M|2. A|it|The main character, defined by the reference im — describe their appearance once and fully here
M|2. A|- Th|location, architectural or natural context, spatial scale
M|2. A|it|Lighting condition and time of day
M|2. A|it|Any persistent props, surfaces, or spatial landmarks that shots will reference
M|2. A|tx|After the anchor, **do not restate appearance**. Use space, landmarks, and orientation to locate the character instead.
M|2. A|tx|---
M|3. S|A nu|
M|3. S|it|Describes **one clear, visible moment**
M|3. S|it|Starts w/ a **framing tag** (see vocabulary below)
M|3. S|it|Contains **one main verb**. Secondary motion is implied, not listed.
M|3. S|it|Ends w/ its **duration in seconds** (e.g. `→ 3s`)
M|3. S|it|Appends `[cut]` when the transition is a cut; omit otherwise
M|3. S|tx|**Shot durations must sum exactly to the total duration.**
M|3. S|**Fr|**
M|3. S|tx|`Wide shot` · `md shot` · `Close-up` · `md close-up` · `Profile view` · `Side view` · `Two-shot` · `Over-the-shoulder`
M|3. S|**Mo|**
M|3. S|it|Camera movement only when explicitly stated by the us. Do not add it by default.
M|3. S|it|Do not describe camera mechanics (pan speed, focal length, rack focus) unless essential.
M|3. S|it|Do NOT use non-human POVs, macro perspectives, or abstract viewpoints.
M|3. S|it|Preserve body orientation across shots. Change orientation only if the action explicitly requires it.
M|3. S|**Pa|**
M|3. S|- Do|2–3 strong shots, not many small ones.
M|3. S|it|Do not explain emotion, intention, or symbolism. Show physical action only.
M|3. S|it|Clarity, physical continuity, and readable motion take priority over coverage.
M|3. S|tx|---
M|4. S|One |
M|4. S|it|Ambient environment sounds
M|4. S|it|Music style or instrument
M|4. S|it|Sonic texture (e.g. vinyl crackle, room reverb, open-air resonance)
M|4. S|tx|Do not describe per-shot sound effects. This is the overall soundscape.
M|4. S|> **|** Sound: soft ambient piano, distant city hum, warm vinyl crackle.
M|4. S|tx|---
M|Dura|Befo|
M|Dura|- Op|20–25% of total
M|Dura|- Co|50–60% of total
M|Dura|- Cl|20–25% of total
M|Dura|tx|Adjust for pacing feel. **The sum must match the total duration exactly.** State durations as whole or half seconds (e.g. 2s, 2.5s, 3s).
M|Dura|tx|---
M|Full|**In|** Reference im of a woman in her 30s w/ dark curly hair, cream linen dress. Setting: a sunlit Parisian café terrace, late morning. Action: she sits down, reads a letter, and smiles. Duration: 9s.
M|Full|tx|---
M|Full|**Ou|**
M|Full|Styl|Romantic editorial film, 2020s Parisian aesthetic, soft diffused morning light, warm cream and sage tones, shallow depth of field, 16:9, subtle film grain.
M|Full|tx|A woman in her mid-thirties w/ dark curly hair, wearing a cream linen dress. She is seated at a small round marble bistro table on a sun-dappled café terrace. Iron chairs and potted herbs border the frame. Late-morning light filters through canvas awnings overhead, casting soft warm shadows across the stone floor.
M|Full|tx|1. Wide shot — she approaches the terrace from the left and settles into the chair → 2s [cut]
M|Full|tx|2. md shot — she pulls a folded letter from a small cloth bag on the table → 2s [cut]
M|Full|tx|3. Close-up — her eyes move across the page, expression still → 2s [cut]
M|Full|tx|4. md close-up — a slow smile crosses her face as she lowers the letter → 3s
M|Full|Soun|distant café ambience, light acoustic guitar, soft clinking of porcelain.
M|Full|tx|---
M|Edge|- **|** Ask before generating. Character description alone is insufficient for Kling 3.0 consistency.
M|Edge|- **|** Use half-second increments (2.5s, 1.5s) to hit the target exactly.
M|Edge|- **|** Consolidate into 2–3 strong shots. Avoid listing every sub-movement.
M|Edge|- **|** Anchor in physical, observable action. Do not interpret or symbolize.
M|Edge|- **|16):** Note in the style line. Favor tighter framings (md, close-up) over wides.
M|Edge|- **|** Output the full four-part structure as plain text w/ no markdown formatting inside the pm itself — the style line, anchor paragraph, shot list, and sound line flow directly into the Kling node.